Thanks for your helpful advice!

When you say to &quot;only catch exceptions that I expect&quot; do you mean for test cases where the proper behaviour of the method under test is to throw a particular exception?  Your example shows a &quot;return&quot; in the catch block so I would think that is a &quot;test passed&quot; result. 

I&#39;ll look at the AssertionFailedError with great interest -- the lack of an accurate stacktrace is so frustrating!

John


